Sentencas: To limit oxidation and protect against loss of conductivity in stainless steel for applications such as high temperature fuel cell interconnects, a layer of cobalt was electroplated on the surface.
Titulo: Cobalt plating of high temperature stainless steel interconnects

Sentencas: When heated in air at 800 degrees C, the cobalt was converted into spinel phases containing cobalt, chromium and iron.
Titulo: Cobalt plating of high temperature stainless steel interconnects

Sentencas: The oxide layer was characterized by X-ray diffraction and energy dispersive spectrometry.
Titulo: Cobalt plating of high temperature stainless steel interconnects

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of the samples was measured by a new technique.
Titulo: Cobalt plating of high temperature stainless steel interconnects

Sentencas: After 1900 It oxidation at 800 degrees C in air, the cobalt-coated UNS430 stainless steel had a clean surface and a stable ASR of 0.026 Omega cm(2) compared to uncoated UNS430 which showed a thick, porous oxide growth and an ASR more than 10-fold higher.
Titulo: Cobalt plating of high temperature stainless steel interconnects
